page.title: 10Nature
page.content: There are often rabbits around the fenland in Gedney Hill.They are quite popular around here. The birds common to this area are swallows,swans,herons,jackdaws, swifts,crows,thrushes,pheasants and black birds.We get quite a few birds around here because we don't get a lot of traffic on the roads and it is quiet. I have got a partridge and a skylark nesting quietly in my garden. Foxes are seen quite a lot at night.The fox is a carnivorous creature and eats: chickens,geese, pheasants,hares and rabbits etc.. Around Gedney Hill they are sometimes seen carrying things off in their mouths. Many mice are found in the area, particularly in dustbins,rubbish-dumps and other unhealthy places.
